      <p>In addition to the area model, whole number multiplication by skip counting can be adapted for fraction multiplication. Consider the following example of whole number skip counting (or repeated addition: 3+3+3+3+3+3 =18, or 6x3 =18:</p>
      <figure id="fig3"  class="center">
